1
00:00:13,221 --> 00:00:15,015
Fifty years ago,

2
00:00:15,098 --> 00:00:18,518
a woman wasn't considered "matured"

3
00:00:19,019 --> 00:00:21,479
until she got married and had children.

4
00:00:22,188 --> 00:00:24,482
I'm not sure that much has changed.

5
00:00:25,316 --> 00:00:26,443
You're right.

6
00:00:27,819 --> 00:00:30,947
But either way,
marriage didn't seem like something

7
00:00:31,031 --> 00:00:33,241
that was in the cards
at that point in my life.

8
00:00:33,324 --> 00:00:35,952
And Kazusa had only been open
for a year at that point.

9
00:00:36,036 --> 00:00:36,870
Mm-hmm.

10
00:00:36,953 --> 00:00:38,580
Did you find
running a hotel more appealing

11
00:00:38,663 --> 00:00:39,914
than owning a club in Ginza?

12
00:00:42,083 --> 00:00:44,127
Kawatani, are you married?

13
00:00:44,210 --> 00:00:45,336
Oh.

14
00:00:45,420 --> 00:00:47,422
Unfortunately,
I still haven't found the right woman,

15
00:00:47,505 --> 00:00:49,090
but I haven't stopped looking.

16
00:00:50,884 --> 00:00:52,844
How about you? Are you married?

17
00:00:53,720 --> 00:00:55,388
Uh, yeah, actually.

18
00:00:55,472 --> 00:00:56,681
Hmm.

19
00:00:59,434 --> 00:01:01,770
At the end of the day,
marriage is more an impulsive decision

20
00:01:01,853 --> 00:01:04,022
than a logical one, don't you agree?

21
00:01:04,981 --> 00:01:07,108
Yeah. I agree.

22
00:01:10,403 --> 00:01:12,572
Hey. Are you two hungry?

23
00:01:12,655 --> 00:01:14,699
Uh, a bit.

24
00:01:14,783 --> 00:01:16,326
Let me cook for you.

25
00:01:16,409 --> 00:01:17,994
I will make you my specialty.

26
00:01:18,078 --> 00:01:19,996
Oh, no! You don't have to do that.

27
00:01:20,080 --> 00:01:22,999
Oh, really, ma'am. It… it's not necessary.

28
00:01:23,083 --> 00:01:25,210
Uh, what is your specialty?

29
00:01:25,293 --> 00:01:26,169
<i>Oyakodon.</i>

30
00:01:50,193 --> 00:01:51,027
Uh…

31
00:01:53,113 --> 00:01:54,405
Kazuko, uh…

32
00:01:54,906 --> 00:01:55,782
Yes?

33
00:01:56,449 --> 00:01:58,535
Uh, it's just that, uh…

34
00:02:00,787 --> 00:02:02,122
It's my first time.

35
00:02:03,957 --> 00:02:04,791
Oh.

36
00:02:11,589 --> 00:02:12,882
Why don't we start

37
00:02:13,716 --> 00:02:15,635
by getting under the futon?

38
00:02:15,718 --> 00:02:16,553
Okay.

39
00:02:24,185 --> 00:02:25,979
- Go on.
- Okay, and you, uh…

40
00:02:46,291 --> 00:02:48,668
That was great.

41
00:02:59,721 --> 00:03:02,015
So what's the plan for tomorrow?

42
00:03:03,892 --> 00:03:04,893
Huh?

43
00:03:05,894 --> 00:03:06,978
What's the plan?

44
00:03:08,313 --> 00:03:09,522
What do we do next?

45
00:03:10,440 --> 00:03:11,482
Ah.

46
00:03:12,734 --> 00:03:14,611
I'm making courtesy calls

47
00:03:15,862 --> 00:03:17,739
to government offices

48
00:03:18,239 --> 00:03:20,116
and local banks and whatnot.

49
00:03:23,620 --> 00:03:26,164
I wouldn't mind tagging along
with you as well.

50
00:03:27,040 --> 00:03:29,667
Hey. You'd be okay with that,
wouldn't you?

51
00:03:30,793 --> 00:03:32,128
Of course I would.

52
00:03:33,504 --> 00:03:37,133
My chance to present you
to everyone as my wife.

53
00:03:40,511 --> 00:03:41,638
Kazuko.

54
00:03:42,722 --> 00:03:43,890
What is it?

55
00:03:44,557 --> 00:03:46,976
Please, let's do it again.

56
00:04:03,243 --> 00:04:04,953
All right.

57
00:04:09,249 --> 00:04:11,209
There we are.

58
00:04:13,544 --> 00:04:15,922
Ah. Still not up yet?

59
00:04:16,005 --> 00:04:18,466
- Nah. Talk about an easy life.
- Yeah.

60
00:05:18,901 --> 00:05:19,902
Oh.

61
00:05:22,280 --> 00:05:24,032
Good morning, young madam.

62
00:05:24,115 --> 00:05:25,950
Good morning. Where's my husband?

63
00:05:26,034 --> 00:05:27,160
Excuse me.

64
00:05:35,877 --> 00:05:37,879
Good morning, Kazuko.

65
00:05:37,962 --> 00:05:38,963
Oh.

66
00:05:39,047 --> 00:05:40,381
Oh, Mother.

67
00:05:40,465 --> 00:05:42,008
I'm so sorry I overslept.

68
00:05:42,091 --> 00:05:45,428
It's all right.
I'd imagine you were exhausted.

69
00:05:46,220 --> 00:05:47,055
Uh…

70
00:05:48,639 --> 00:05:50,767
A bit of breakfast will do the trick.

71
00:05:51,476 --> 00:05:53,561
Ah, no. Marohiko left already?

72
00:05:53,644 --> 00:05:55,772
Yes, he's gone to work, of course.

73
00:05:55,855 --> 00:05:58,733
It's just we agreed
that I'd give him a hand with his work.

74
00:05:58,816 --> 00:06:01,652
That's kind of you, though not necessary.

75
00:06:03,488 --> 00:06:05,198
Now just sit down and eat.

76
00:06:37,021 --> 00:06:40,358
Matsue! How dare you make
our young madam do work!

77
00:06:40,441 --> 00:06:42,193
I am so sorry, madam!

78
00:06:42,276 --> 00:06:43,903
Please, forgive us.

79
00:06:45,530 --> 00:06:47,323
We apologize, ma'am,

80
00:06:48,950 --> 00:06:50,743
but we must insist.

81
00:06:51,369 --> 00:06:54,330
Please allow us to complete
our assigned duties here.

82
00:06:55,623 --> 00:06:57,166
I apologize.

83
00:06:58,334 --> 00:07:00,211
Kazuko, come with me.

84
00:07:48,468 --> 00:07:51,596
It's time you understood
what is expected of you in this union.

85
00:07:51,679 --> 00:07:54,140
You have but one important task here.

86
00:07:54,891 --> 00:07:59,353
You chose to marry into this family,
which has lived here for 12 generations.

87
00:07:59,937 --> 00:08:02,648
The duty that is expected of you, Kazuko,

88
00:08:03,149 --> 00:08:05,485
is to ensure that family line carries on.

89
00:08:05,568 --> 00:08:07,361
Do you understand?

90
00:08:08,446 --> 00:08:09,489
I do.

91
00:08:26,714 --> 00:08:27,882
Kazuko, um,

92
00:08:28,966 --> 00:08:30,092
I was wondering.

93
00:08:30,176 --> 00:08:31,886
How many children do you want?

94
00:08:32,929 --> 00:08:36,599
I ask because I felt so lonely
growing up without siblings.

95
00:08:37,517 --> 00:08:39,519
So I'd love to have a lot of children.

96
00:08:39,602 --> 00:08:41,437
Enough to have our own baseball team.

97
00:08:47,693 --> 00:08:49,320
Listen, Marohiko.

98
00:08:50,613 --> 00:08:51,822
The thing is,

99
00:08:52,323 --> 00:08:56,118
I'd like to help you with the business
that you're gonna start.

100
00:08:58,454 --> 00:09:01,415
As you know,
I have a lot of experience in the area

101
00:09:01,499 --> 00:09:04,293
of entertaining
very important men in Ginza.

102
00:09:05,044 --> 00:09:08,214
I think I can be instrumental to you
in this whole process.

103
00:09:08,798 --> 00:09:12,093
We… we discussed this. You wanted us
to chase our dreams together.

104
00:09:12,176 --> 00:09:13,344
Kazuko.

105
00:09:14,262 --> 00:09:16,264
Our first priority is children.

106
00:09:17,014 --> 00:09:17,932
Okay?

107
00:09:23,437 --> 00:09:25,523
Now, come on. Come here.

108
00:10:08,774 --> 00:10:11,110
Our eggs here are delicious, aren't they?

109
00:10:11,193 --> 00:10:12,153
Mm.

110
00:10:12,862 --> 00:10:14,905
It's a long-standing tradition
in our family

111
00:10:14,989 --> 00:10:17,867
to eat freshly laid eggs every day.

112
00:10:17,950 --> 00:10:21,412
It's a symbol of the prosperity
of the Mita family.

113
00:10:29,170 --> 00:10:30,421
Uh, Mother?

114
00:10:31,631 --> 00:10:33,674
Yes, Kazuko, dear?

115
00:10:35,343 --> 00:10:36,218
Um…

116
00:10:39,555 --> 00:10:43,934
Would you please allow me to help out
with some of the work around here?

117
00:10:44,685 --> 00:10:46,354
Laundry or cleaning.

118
00:10:46,437 --> 00:10:47,521
I'd like to do more.

119
00:10:48,272 --> 00:10:51,108
Uh, I can assure you
I'm a good cook as well.

120
00:10:51,192 --> 00:10:54,570
So what if I made a nice dinner
for you and Marohiko tonight?

121
00:10:54,654 --> 00:10:57,198
I think not.
Our housemaids look after all that.

122
00:10:58,240 --> 00:11:03,621
Mm. Yes, but it's important
I stay active, or I'll be out of shape.

123
00:11:03,704 --> 00:11:05,206
For a pregnancy.

124
00:11:05,706 --> 00:11:07,333
All right.

125
00:11:08,042 --> 00:11:12,171
Then how about
you take care of our prized chickens?

126
00:11:13,214 --> 00:11:14,423
Ah.

127
00:11:16,300 --> 00:11:18,844
We feed them three times a day.
Morning, noon, and evening.

128
00:11:18,928 --> 00:11:21,681
Please make sure
to change their water with each feeding.

129
00:11:21,764 --> 00:11:24,058
We let them out
between two and four in the afternoon

130
00:11:24,141 --> 00:11:25,726
so that we can clean the coop.

131
00:11:26,227 --> 00:11:29,980
Please make sure you keep it clean,
or madam will be very angry.

132
00:11:33,693 --> 00:11:35,611
Thank you. I'll get it done.

133
00:11:36,320 --> 00:11:39,407
I'm so sorry.
You shouldn't have to do any of this.

134
00:11:39,490 --> 00:11:41,242
Oh, no. Don't you worry.

135
00:11:41,325 --> 00:11:42,993
It's a nice change of pace.

136
00:11:45,663 --> 00:11:46,580
Oh.

137
00:11:53,546 --> 00:11:56,507
Almost magical
how they're always laying eggs.

138
00:11:58,801 --> 00:12:01,137
All right. Come on, now. Get out, get out!

139
00:12:01,220 --> 00:12:04,932
Ah, eh. No! Come on.
Not that way. Here, go on.

140
00:12:05,516 --> 00:12:06,392
Get out!

141
00:12:08,227 --> 00:12:09,603
Come on, you guys.

142
00:12:09,687 --> 00:12:12,356
No! Not there!
I need you all out. Go on, go on!

143
00:12:34,754 --> 00:12:36,172
Kazuko.

144
00:12:37,465 --> 00:12:38,382
Hmm?

145
00:12:40,593 --> 00:12:41,969
What are you doing?

146
00:12:42,678 --> 00:12:44,472
Come on. Get over here.

147
00:12:49,602 --> 00:12:51,187
I, uh…

148
00:12:51,270 --> 00:12:52,646
Just a second.

149
00:13:08,954 --> 00:13:10,164
Kazusa Club.

150
00:13:10,247 --> 00:13:11,373
<i>Hisao?</i>

151
00:13:11,457 --> 00:13:13,083
Kazuko!

152
00:13:13,167 --> 00:13:15,085
<i>How's the club going? Everything okay?</i>

153
00:13:15,169 --> 00:13:16,796
Good, good. Very good.

154
00:13:16,879 --> 00:13:19,465
<i>The customers keep saying</i>
<i>how much they miss you, of course.</i>

155
00:13:19,548 --> 00:13:21,217
Oh?

156
00:13:21,926 --> 00:13:23,010
<i>What about you?</i>

157
00:13:23,594 --> 00:13:25,012
<i>How's everything over there?</i>

158
00:13:26,388 --> 00:13:27,556
Mm.

159
00:13:28,140 --> 00:13:29,225
All right.

160
00:13:30,226 --> 00:13:32,311
Ah, you know how--

161
00:13:37,441 --> 00:13:39,235
Can you please not make
long-distance calls

162
00:13:39,318 --> 00:13:41,612
if you're going to engage
in useless chit-chat?

163
00:13:44,615 --> 00:13:47,701
Now run along. Your husband
is waiting for you in the bedroom.

164
00:13:58,003 --> 00:14:00,256
Here ya go. No, no, no. Share.

165
00:14:00,339 --> 00:14:01,841
There.

166
00:14:05,678 --> 00:14:07,054
When I was younger,

167
00:14:07,638 --> 00:14:09,890
my job was to take care of them.

168
00:14:09,974 --> 00:14:11,100
They're cute, right?

169
00:14:11,809 --> 00:14:12,977
- Marohiko.
- Huh?

170
00:14:13,060 --> 00:14:16,939
I just got word that your granduncle
in Mishima has passed away.

171
00:14:17,022 --> 00:14:18,274
He did?

172
00:14:18,357 --> 00:14:19,525
I see.

173
00:14:19,608 --> 00:14:20,943
Did he attend our wedding?

174
00:14:21,026 --> 00:14:24,154
No. He'd been bedridden
for some time, so he never--

175
00:14:24,238 --> 00:14:26,156
Stop wasting time.
You need to get ready now.

176
00:14:26,240 --> 00:14:28,033
Oh. Okay.

177
00:14:28,617 --> 00:14:31,287
I'm so sorry, Mother.
I'll pack my mourning clothes right away.

178
00:14:31,370 --> 00:14:33,163
You will not be joining us.

179
00:14:46,927 --> 00:14:48,596
- I'll see you soon.
- Safe trip.

180
00:15:21,503 --> 00:15:22,963
I can't say I blame her.

181
00:15:23,047 --> 00:15:24,965
It would be far too embarrassing for madam

182
00:15:25,049 --> 00:15:28,594
to let that sort of woman
be seen with her out in public.

183
00:15:28,677 --> 00:15:32,056
I have no idea what she did
back in Ginza or wherever she came from,

184
00:15:32,139 --> 00:15:36,185
but she had the nerve to offer
her assistance to young master's work.

185
00:15:37,686 --> 00:15:41,065
Well, once she births an heir,
they'll have no more use for her.

186
00:15:41,148 --> 00:15:42,107
Uh-huh.

187
00:15:42,608 --> 00:15:44,818
Madam is already planning
to throw her out.

188
00:15:44,902 --> 00:15:46,820
I'm sure.

189
00:15:46,904 --> 00:15:51,408
I heard that master told his mother
that if he couldn't marry her, he'd die.

190
00:15:51,492 --> 00:15:53,369
- Is that true?
- Oh, yes.

191
00:15:53,452 --> 00:15:55,371
Poor man is sheltered and so naive.

192
00:15:55,454 --> 00:15:57,581
He's completely infatuated
with that hussy.

193
00:15:57,665 --> 00:16:00,125
She's got it so easy.
Far more than she deserves.

194
00:16:00,209 --> 00:16:01,961
All she has to do is bear his child.

195
00:16:02,044 --> 00:16:02,878
Yes.

196
00:16:02,962 --> 00:16:04,672
She's no different than a chicken.

197
00:16:04,755 --> 00:16:06,090
A chicken. You're right.

198
00:16:06,173 --> 00:16:08,968
No wonder she wanted to care for them.

199
00:16:10,928 --> 00:16:12,554
You are all

200
00:16:14,348 --> 00:16:16,308
immediately dismissed.

201
00:16:17,518 --> 00:16:19,520
Miss, listen…

202
00:16:19,603 --> 00:16:22,439
Are you three disobeying a direct order?

203
00:16:22,523 --> 00:16:24,191
Lord, do you hear this woman?

204
00:16:24,274 --> 00:16:27,528
Forgive us, miss, but you don't
have the authority to do that.

205
00:16:27,611 --> 00:16:30,531
Get out, or you'll see
what this hussy is capable of!

206
00:16:52,594 --> 00:16:53,721
What's going on?

207
00:16:56,348 --> 00:16:59,727
They left the gate wide open.
I'll need to have a word with them.

208
00:16:59,810 --> 00:17:01,103
Yeah. You should.

209
00:17:01,603 --> 00:17:02,646
Hello?

210
00:17:09,695 --> 00:17:10,821
It's pitch-dark.

211
00:17:13,824 --> 00:17:16,285
- What is going on here?
- Hello?

212
00:17:17,786 --> 00:17:20,456
- Is anyone here?
- Kazuko?

213
00:17:21,707 --> 00:17:22,833
Kazuko?

214
00:17:23,751 --> 00:17:25,002
Kazuko!

215
00:17:27,838 --> 00:17:28,922
Kazuko?

216
00:17:29,923 --> 00:17:31,175
Kazuko?

217
00:17:39,183 --> 00:17:40,350
What is this?

218
00:18:00,996 --> 00:18:02,039
Huh?

219
00:18:30,400 --> 00:18:32,945
Kazuko. What have you done?

220
00:19:02,766 --> 00:19:03,934
Putrid.

221
00:19:04,601 --> 00:19:07,855
Poultry that lay that many eggs
are so bland.

222
00:19:18,907 --> 00:19:22,035
The meat from a rooster.
Firm and delicious.

223
00:19:35,716 --> 00:19:37,551
Sorry, I don't mean to laugh.

224
00:19:37,634 --> 00:19:40,387
It's just, I'd say it served them right.

225
00:19:41,054 --> 00:19:42,973
Oh yes. It served them right.

226
00:19:44,641 --> 00:19:45,934
I love that.

227
00:19:46,977 --> 00:19:50,397
I knew that story
would most likely hit home for you.

228
00:19:50,480 --> 00:19:51,315
What?

229
00:19:51,899 --> 00:19:54,401
Well, your ex-husband,
who's also your old editor,

230
00:19:54,484 --> 00:19:56,653
once told you, you have no talent.

231
00:19:56,737 --> 00:19:58,530
He said,
“You should give up being a novelist

232
00:19:58,614 --> 00:20:00,616
and concentrate on being a mother.”

233
00:20:01,158 --> 00:20:04,912
Then you said,
"Not a damn chance," and divorced him.

234
00:20:09,917 --> 00:20:12,294
You can't hide anything from me.

235
00:20:13,337 --> 00:20:16,882
It seems… you're not my biggest fan,
are you?

236
00:20:20,302 --> 00:20:25,474
You don't want to write a trashy novel
about a cruel, fraudulent psychic.

237
00:20:25,557 --> 00:20:30,103
But you're also desperate to publish
that elusive second novel.

238
00:20:30,604 --> 00:20:32,940
And you're worried
if you let this opportunity slip away,

239
00:20:33,023 --> 00:20:35,734
your writing career
will be as good as dead.

240
00:20:35,817 --> 00:20:37,069
I'm right, aren't I?

241
00:20:40,197 --> 00:20:41,782
I know all about you, Minori.

242
00:20:41,865 --> 00:20:46,328
You were born on July 12, 1969,
under the Martian Minus.

243
00:20:46,411 --> 00:20:48,705
The good news
is that your Great Calamity period

244
00:20:48,789 --> 00:20:49,748
ended last year.

245
00:20:51,083 --> 00:20:54,586
All I see for you
is continuously growing good fortune.

246
00:20:56,546 --> 00:20:58,048
So now, Minori?

247
00:20:59,174 --> 00:21:00,008
Yes.

248
00:21:00,759 --> 00:21:03,387
I need you to listen to my life story.

249
00:21:04,096 --> 00:21:06,265
It's a good one, I promise you.

250
00:21:07,891 --> 00:21:10,769
You'll write a great novel
and go back to your worthless ex-husband

251
00:21:10,852 --> 00:21:12,145
and tell him to "suck it."

252
00:21:23,949 --> 00:21:26,118
Now, shall we eat?

253
00:21:27,619 --> 00:21:28,704
Bless this meal.

254
00:21:29,204 --> 00:21:31,039
Bless this meal.

255
00:21:35,502 --> 00:21:37,337
Mmm! Good!

256
00:21:40,132 --> 00:21:41,049
Mmm.

257
00:21:47,723 --> 00:21:49,391
Bye-bye, everyone!

258
00:21:49,474 --> 00:21:51,810
He said "bye-bye."
Say "bye-bye." Go on, say "bye-bye."

259
00:21:54,354 --> 00:21:56,189
- Goodbye.
- Have a nice day.

260
00:22:07,617 --> 00:22:08,827
Hey, what's up?

261
00:22:08,910 --> 00:22:12,748
<i>Hey, uh, listen, something came up.</i>
<i>I gotta work this weekend.</i>

262
00:22:12,831 --> 00:22:16,335
<i>I'm sorry to do this, but can we move</i>
<i>Reina's sleepover to next week?</i>

263
00:22:18,420 --> 00:22:21,590
I say we just cancel it for now.
Sorry, but that's on you.

264
00:22:22,174 --> 00:22:24,301
<i>But Reina was looking forward to it too.</i>

265
00:22:26,261 --> 00:22:28,180
Yeah, but that's not my problem.

266
00:22:28,263 --> 00:22:30,766
I'll let Reina know you're busy.
Talk soon.

267
00:22:30,849 --> 00:22:32,142
<i>Minori, wait.</i>

268
00:22:32,225 --> 00:22:33,185
What is it?

269
00:22:34,311 --> 00:22:37,189
<i>Is it true you're writing</i>
<i>a biography on Kazuko Hosoki?</i>

270
00:22:38,440 --> 00:22:39,649
Where did you hear that?

271
00:22:40,150 --> 00:22:42,903
<i>People are saying Hosoki herself</i>
<i>has been bragging about it.</i>

272
00:22:44,196 --> 00:22:46,740
<i>What are you trying to accomplish</i>
<i>writing something like that?</i>

273
00:22:48,283 --> 00:22:49,701
<i>Is it the money?</i>

274
00:22:49,785 --> 00:22:52,329
<i>I told you I'm willing</i>
<i>to pay more child support.</i>

275
00:22:52,412 --> 00:22:54,373
<i>You need to stop being</i>
<i>so stubborn about this.</i>

276
00:22:54,456 --> 00:22:55,832
<i>If you need some extra--</i>

277
00:22:58,001 --> 00:22:59,211
Mommy!

278
00:22:59,294 --> 00:23:01,421
There she is. Come here.

279
00:23:01,505 --> 00:23:02,464
I got you.

280
00:23:06,385 --> 00:23:08,637
- Reina.
- Yeah?

281
00:23:10,055 --> 00:23:12,265
Mommy's going to work hard, okay?

282
00:23:13,725 --> 00:23:15,477
She's going to write a great novel.

283
00:23:16,019 --> 00:23:16,895
Cool!

284
00:23:17,521 --> 00:23:19,773
Just do your best. Okay, Mommy?

285
00:23:21,900 --> 00:23:23,527
Yes. I'll do my best!

286
00:23:27,322 --> 00:23:28,448
Ah!

287
00:23:29,116 --> 00:23:31,201
Look out! Here comes the tunnel!

288
00:23:31,701 --> 00:23:34,287
<i>I love him, I love him, I love him…</i>

289
00:23:34,371 --> 00:23:36,206
Mommy, do your best!

290
00:23:36,289 --> 00:23:38,125
- Mommy, do your best!
- I will!

291
00:23:38,208 --> 00:23:40,836
- Mommy, do your best!
- Thank you, sweetheart!

292
00:23:42,087 --> 00:23:46,216
<i>Follow him, wherever he may go…</i>

293
00:23:46,800 --> 00:23:49,928
<i>Back in Tokyo,</i>
<i>construction was happening everywhere.</i>

294
00:23:50,011 --> 00:23:53,140
<i>Everyone was trying</i>
<i>to get things done before the Olympics.</i>

295
00:23:53,223 --> 00:23:56,226
<i>The silence at Mita's</i>
<i>almost didn't feel real</i>

296
00:23:56,309 --> 00:23:58,478
<i>compared to how deafening the city was.</i>

297
00:23:58,562 --> 00:24:00,814
<i>But I didn't mind that at all.</i>

298
00:24:02,149 --> 00:24:05,694
<i>Watching the city being rebuilt</i>
<i>was incredibly exciting.</i>

299
00:24:06,611 --> 00:24:09,197
<i>I told myself to forget about Mita</i>

300
00:24:09,698 --> 00:24:12,367
<i>and start working towards my next goal.</i>

301
00:24:13,535 --> 00:24:17,914
LET’S SUPPORT THE OLYMPICS NOW
ACCEPTING DONATIONS FOR THE OLYMPICS

302
00:24:17,998 --> 00:24:24,588
TOKYO, OUR HOME
LET’S MAKE NEXT YEAR’S OLYMPICS A SUCCESS

303
00:24:28,049 --> 00:24:30,510
- Here you go.
- Oh, thank you. Appreciate it.

304
00:24:33,513 --> 00:24:35,140
Thank you very much.

305
00:24:36,892 --> 00:24:40,061
I'm not gonna lie. I thought you'd be gone
longer than a week.

306
00:24:40,145 --> 00:24:41,938
Don't you know
the golden rule of business?

307
00:24:42,022 --> 00:24:43,356
Be quick to cut your losses.

308
00:24:43,440 --> 00:24:47,152
Oh, cut your losses, huh?
Kazuko, I expect nothing less from you.

309
00:24:47,235 --> 00:24:50,030
Well, doing business
is my primary strength, after all.

310
00:24:50,113 --> 00:24:52,491
Oh, well,
that explains why you wasted no time

311
00:24:52,574 --> 00:24:54,701
opening up two more clubs in Ginza.

312
00:24:54,784 --> 00:24:55,827
Correct.

313
00:24:55,911 --> 00:24:59,664
Next year, a countless number of people
will be flocking to Tokyo,

314
00:25:00,290 --> 00:25:02,751
and Ginza's right in the middle
of that gold mine.

315
00:25:03,293 --> 00:25:05,921
You can't expect me not to take advantage
of that Olympic boom.

316
00:25:06,004 --> 00:25:08,006
Oh, sis, nothing can keep you down.

317
00:25:08,089 --> 00:25:09,466
Kazuko, I'm telling you.

318
00:25:09,549 --> 00:25:11,885
You should have
the fortune teller give you a reading.

319
00:25:11,968 --> 00:25:13,595
Everyone says he's spot on.

320
00:25:13,678 --> 00:25:15,847
Mom, you need to stop going on about that.

321
00:25:15,931 --> 00:25:19,267
Fortune-telling is a scam.
He's taking everyone for a ride.

322
00:25:20,101 --> 00:25:23,230
You've wasted so much of your time
serving <i>oden </i>in this back alley

323
00:25:23,313 --> 00:25:25,774
that you're out of touch
with the real world.

324
00:25:29,611 --> 00:25:30,695
Kazuko.

325
00:25:31,947 --> 00:25:33,865
Why would you say something like that?

326
00:25:39,996 --> 00:25:41,957
I'm sorry. I didn't…

327
00:25:42,040 --> 00:25:44,000
I went too far, Mom.

328
00:25:53,552 --> 00:25:55,637
I understand your concern, Mine,

329
00:25:56,221 --> 00:25:57,764
but your daughter's right.

330
00:25:57,847 --> 00:26:00,308
It's the perfect time
to expand the business.

331
00:26:04,771 --> 00:26:06,314
Now that you mention it,

332
00:26:06,398 --> 00:26:09,859
a bank rep actually spoke to me
about potentially taking out a loan,

333
00:26:09,943 --> 00:26:12,112
but… but I'd rather

334
00:26:12,696 --> 00:26:15,448
continue working with you in that regard.

335
00:26:16,783 --> 00:26:18,952
You've made me a lot of money, Kazuko.

336
00:26:19,452 --> 00:26:20,954
So consider it done.

337
00:26:21,580 --> 00:26:23,665
I really appreciate that.

338
00:26:47,772 --> 00:26:51,192
Uh-huh. Yes, yep. Right away.

339
00:26:51,693 --> 00:26:54,321
Yep. That all sounds good to me. Okay.

340
00:26:54,404 --> 00:26:57,866
I'll make sure to tell her.
Yeah, yeah, yeah. Yup. She'll be thrilled.

341
00:27:09,336 --> 00:27:12,839
I'm sorry to bother you, sir,
but in my last reading,

342
00:27:12,922 --> 00:27:16,509
you told me that my daughter
Kazuko's business ventures would succeed.

343
00:27:16,593 --> 00:27:19,095
Mm. Yes, she will succeed.

344
00:27:19,179 --> 00:27:22,015
In fact,
I said she would achieve great success.

345
00:27:22,682 --> 00:27:26,019
Ah! Ah! Thank you, sir!

346
00:27:26,645 --> 00:27:27,687
Ah.

347
00:27:31,191 --> 00:27:35,111
Wasn't there also something else
that I mentioned to you?

348
00:27:36,988 --> 00:27:40,283
You said
she may be swallowed up by her desires.

349
00:27:42,452 --> 00:27:43,870
Hmm.

350
00:27:44,871 --> 00:27:45,830
Uh…

351
00:27:47,165 --> 00:27:48,208
Hmm.

352
00:27:49,793 --> 00:27:50,877
What?

353
00:28:01,429 --> 00:28:03,014
Thanks! Have a good night. Thanks!

354
00:28:19,030 --> 00:28:21,908
Good evening, sir. This is Haruka.
She's one of our best.

355
00:28:22,534 --> 00:28:23,576
Excuse me, Kazuko?

356
00:28:24,786 --> 00:28:27,163
The underboss
of the Dainihon Kosei-kai is here.

357
00:28:27,247 --> 00:28:29,207
He says it's about a protection racket.

358
00:28:39,092 --> 00:28:40,427
Please excuse me.

359
00:28:49,102 --> 00:28:50,937
I'm sorry to keep you waiting.

360
00:28:51,020 --> 00:28:53,064
I'm Kazuko, the owner of the club.

361
00:28:53,148 --> 00:28:55,024
Yes, I'm Isezaki.

362
00:28:55,108 --> 00:28:58,236
Starting this month,
this whole area is under my jurisdiction.

363
00:28:58,737 --> 00:29:02,657
So from now on,
you'll need to pay us a monthly fee.

364
00:29:02,741 --> 00:29:04,200
And how much is that?

365
00:29:04,784 --> 00:29:05,702
Twenty.

366
00:29:09,038 --> 00:29:11,791
I'm sorry, but that's ten times more
than what we pay now.

367
00:29:12,459 --> 00:29:14,377
I don't imagine money's an issue.

368
00:29:15,170 --> 00:29:16,963
As I hear it,
you're opening two more clubs.

369
00:29:18,423 --> 00:29:20,341
Good news spreads like wildfire.

370
00:29:21,301 --> 00:29:24,137
But isn't 20 pretty steep
for a monthly protection racket?

371
00:29:24,220 --> 00:29:25,346
Oh!

372
00:29:28,850 --> 00:29:30,769
My hand must've slipped.

373
00:29:31,644 --> 00:29:33,229
I'm clumsy that way.

374
00:29:33,938 --> 00:29:37,650
We will not be intimidated
into paying more than a reasonable amount.

375
00:29:37,734 --> 00:29:40,111
Bitch, you need to watch your mouth
and pay up! You got that?

376
00:29:43,406 --> 00:29:45,200
Get out, or I'll call the police.

377
00:29:46,618 --> 00:29:49,037
Oh, you can call them if you want,

378
00:29:50,538 --> 00:29:52,665
but repercussions could follow.

379
00:29:56,127 --> 00:29:57,378
Ojiki.

380
00:29:57,462 --> 00:30:00,006
Good evening, Isezaki.

381
00:30:02,050 --> 00:30:04,928
I'm going to assume
you didn't know I was a regular here?

382
00:30:05,970 --> 00:30:08,264
No, sir. I had no idea.

383
00:30:08,807 --> 00:30:10,183
You should go right now.

384
00:30:12,519 --> 00:30:14,187
Yes, sir. I'm very sorry.

385
00:30:14,687 --> 00:30:15,647
Let's go.

386
00:30:32,205 --> 00:30:35,291
My apologies for the ruckus.
Everything's under control.

387
00:30:35,792 --> 00:30:37,043
Our deepest apologies.

388
00:30:37,126 --> 00:30:39,963
- Our deepest apologies.
- Our deepest apologies.

389
00:30:41,464 --> 00:30:44,843
Sorry. I'm not familiar with you, sir,
but you have my thanks.

390
00:30:45,718 --> 00:30:47,053
I'm Takiguchi.

391
00:30:47,554 --> 00:30:49,597
You know,
a mama of your caliber is hard to find.

392
00:31:00,942 --> 00:31:04,445
<i>When you're alone</i>
<i>And life is making you lonely </i>

393
00:31:04,529 --> 00:31:06,865
<i>You can always go</i>

394
00:31:07,407 --> 00:31:09,033
<i>Downtown</i>

395
00:31:09,117 --> 00:31:12,453
<i>When you've got worries</i>
<i>All the noise and the hurry</i>

396
00:31:12,537 --> 00:31:15,164
<i>Seems to help, I know</i>

397
00:31:15,665 --> 00:31:16,833
<i>Downtown</i>

398
00:31:16,916 --> 00:31:21,170
<i>Just listen to the music</i>
<i>Of the traffic in the city</i>

399
00:31:21,254 --> 00:31:25,008
<i>Linger on the sidewalk</i>
<i>Where the neon signs are pretty</i>

400
00:31:25,091 --> 00:31:27,802
<i>How can you lose?</i>

401
00:31:27,886 --> 00:31:30,763
<i>The lights are much brighter there</i>

402
00:31:30,847 --> 00:31:34,851
<i>You can forget all your troubles</i>
<i>Forget all your cares</i>

403
00:31:34,934 --> 00:31:37,645
<i>So go</i>
<i>Downtown</i>

404
00:31:37,729 --> 00:31:39,647
<i>Things will be great when you're</i>

405
00:31:39,731 --> 00:31:41,441
<i>Downtown…</i>

406
00:31:41,524 --> 00:31:44,027
Well, your club is quite the hot spot.

407
00:31:44,110 --> 00:31:46,988
Thank you.
We're so thrilled you decided to join us.

408
00:31:47,071 --> 00:31:51,409
You're always welcome back at Shinzan,
Dahlia, and Kazusa too.

409
00:31:52,535 --> 00:31:54,954
Oh, I appreciate that. I'll be back.

410
00:31:55,038 --> 00:31:57,332
- Thank you for coming.
- Thank you for coming.

411
00:31:57,415 --> 00:32:01,961
<i>Let your problems surround you</i>
<i>There are movie shows…</i>

412
00:32:02,045 --> 00:32:04,380
- I should check in with things at Dahlia.
- Yes, ma'am.

413
00:32:05,089 --> 00:32:05,924
Take care.

414
00:32:06,007 --> 00:32:10,386
<i>Places to go to</i>
<i>Where they never close</i>

415
00:32:10,470 --> 00:32:11,763
<i>Downtown</i>

416
00:32:11,846 --> 00:32:16,059
<i>Just listen to the rhythm</i>
<i>Of a gentle bossa nova</i>

417
00:32:16,142 --> 00:32:17,936
<i>You'll be dancing with 'em too…</i>

418
00:32:18,770 --> 00:32:19,812
Pardon me.

419
00:32:22,774 --> 00:32:24,359
CLUB DAHLIA

420
00:32:24,442 --> 00:32:26,319
Ah, well, that was a night for the books.

421
00:32:26,402 --> 00:32:28,571
Thank you for coming in. Watch your step.

422
00:32:28,655 --> 00:32:30,990
Ah, nothing like spending the night
with beautiful women.

423
00:32:31,074 --> 00:32:32,784
We look forward to seeing you again.

424
00:32:32,867 --> 00:32:36,537
And just remember, you're always welcome
in Dahlia, Shinzan, and Kazusa too.

425
00:32:36,621 --> 00:32:38,206
Oh, yes. Good to know.

426
00:32:38,289 --> 00:32:39,666
Thank you so much. Good night.

427
00:32:39,749 --> 00:32:41,668
Thank you for coming.

428
00:32:45,630 --> 00:32:47,924
I'm gonna take a peek in Kazusa.
You two can handle things?

429
00:32:48,007 --> 00:32:48,967
Yes

430
00:32:54,055 --> 00:32:55,807
CLUB KAZUSA

431
00:32:56,766 --> 00:32:58,226
<i>Downtown…</i>

432
00:33:03,022 --> 00:33:03,856
- Oh!
- Oh!

433
00:33:03,940 --> 00:33:05,942
- I'm sorry.
- Oh! Oh no, please. It was my fault.

434
00:33:07,443 --> 00:33:09,779
- You all right?
- Yes, sorry.

435
00:33:10,530 --> 00:33:12,865
Hey, Mama!

436
00:33:13,992 --> 00:33:15,785
Oh, good evening, Iizuka-san.

437
00:33:15,868 --> 00:33:17,203
I just came from Shinzan,

438
00:33:17,286 --> 00:33:19,455
and they told me it was too full tonight.

439
00:33:19,539 --> 00:33:20,373
Oh, no.

440
00:33:20,456 --> 00:33:23,668
And then I, uh, tried Dahlia,
and I couldn't get a seat there either.

441
00:33:23,751 --> 00:33:24,711
I'm sorry about that.

442
00:33:24,794 --> 00:33:26,754
It's because both of them
opened just recently.

443
00:33:26,838 --> 00:33:29,757
- Mm-hmm.
- Here. Kazusa would love to have you.

444
00:33:31,509 --> 00:33:33,761
Look at you now with three clubs.

445
00:33:33,845 --> 00:33:35,972
Everyone's raving.
You've become the queen of Ginza.

446
00:33:36,055 --> 00:33:38,683
Oh, stop teasing me, Iizuka-san.
I'm just happy to serve.

447
00:33:38,766 --> 00:33:40,143
No, I'm not kidding. Trust me.

448
00:33:40,226 --> 00:33:42,812
I hear it all,
and you, Mama, are the talk of the town.

449
00:33:42,895 --> 00:33:44,897
It's all over Ginza.

450
00:34:24,562 --> 00:34:25,563
Gentlemen.

451
00:34:25,646 --> 00:34:27,023
Good evening. Hi.

452
00:34:34,197 --> 00:34:35,448
- Take this, please.
- Yes, ma'am.

453
00:34:38,701 --> 00:34:39,952
Here you are. That's for you.

454
00:34:40,036 --> 00:34:41,954
Very generous of you, sir. Thank you.

455
00:34:42,038 --> 00:34:43,748
- Oh.
- That's very kind.

456
00:34:48,836 --> 00:34:51,422
That man over there
just ordered a bottle of Hennessy.

457
00:34:51,506 --> 00:34:52,632
Did you get his card?

458
00:34:52,715 --> 00:34:55,384
Yes. Apparently,
he runs a real estate company.

459
00:34:55,468 --> 00:34:57,011
Things must be going well.

460
00:34:58,971 --> 00:35:01,516
I had a great time tonight.
This is for you.

461
00:35:01,599 --> 00:35:03,226
Oh. You're too kind.

462
00:35:03,309 --> 00:35:05,353
The pleasure was all mine, Sudo-san.

463
00:35:05,436 --> 00:35:07,647
- Here.
- Thank you very much.

464
00:35:09,273 --> 00:35:11,442
We do hope we'll see you again.
Do we have your word?

465
00:35:11,526 --> 00:35:12,360
Mm-hmm.

466
00:35:13,277 --> 00:35:14,529
I'll go say hello.

467
00:35:21,369 --> 00:35:23,412
Forgive me
for not introducing myself earlier.

468
00:35:23,496 --> 00:35:24,789
I'm Kazuko, the mama here.

469
00:35:24,872 --> 00:35:26,082
Uh, Sudo.

470
00:35:26,165 --> 00:35:27,875
Did we not run into each other
the other day?

471
00:35:27,959 --> 00:35:29,544
Yes. Excuse me.

472
00:35:32,839 --> 00:35:34,132
Thank you for coming in.

473
00:35:36,759 --> 00:35:40,221
Two for one sale
on all our winter items! Don't miss out!

474
00:35:40,304 --> 00:35:42,140
- Holiday cakes!
- Only the very best cakes.

475
00:35:42,932 --> 00:35:44,433
You sure you don't wanna try one on?

476
00:35:44,517 --> 00:35:46,602
We stock only the best materials!

477
00:35:51,482 --> 00:35:54,777
<i>Don we now our gay apparel</i>

478
00:35:54,861 --> 00:35:58,698
<i>Fa la la la la, la la la la, la la la</i>

479
00:35:58,781 --> 00:36:02,160
<i>Troll the ancient Yuletide carol…</i>

480
00:36:03,202 --> 00:36:05,288
- Welcome, sir.
- Good evening. Thank you.

481
00:36:05,371 --> 00:36:07,665
Thank you for joining us.
Let me take those for you.

482
00:36:07,748 --> 00:36:09,292
If you'll excuse me a moment.

483
00:36:10,418 --> 00:36:11,878
Thank you, sir. Please enjoy.

484
00:36:11,961 --> 00:36:13,379
Welcome, sir.

485
00:36:14,672 --> 00:36:17,925
It's such a treat to see you
back here again, Sudo-san.

486
00:36:18,926 --> 00:36:20,845
- Here. I'll escort you.
- Hang on.

487
00:36:21,345 --> 00:36:22,180
What is it?

488
00:36:22,680 --> 00:36:26,225
May I request Miyuki and Megumi
to sit with me tonight?

489
00:36:28,144 --> 00:36:29,353
Of course you may.

490
00:36:29,854 --> 00:36:32,857
Thank you so much for joining us.
We'll see you again soon.

491
00:36:44,744 --> 00:36:46,370
Here you go. Please keep the change.

492
00:36:46,454 --> 00:36:48,206
Incredibly generous as always, sir.

493
00:36:48,289 --> 00:36:49,540
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

494
00:36:52,752 --> 00:36:53,711
Here.

495
00:36:53,794 --> 00:36:55,504
You're so kind. Thank you.

496
00:36:55,588 --> 00:36:56,881
And for you as well.

497
00:36:56,964 --> 00:36:59,383
Thank you. You truly are a gentleman.

498
00:37:00,551 --> 00:37:03,095
Sudo's really taken a liking to them,
hasn't he?

499
00:37:05,181 --> 00:37:08,017
Wait. Are you jealous of those two?

500
00:37:08,517 --> 00:37:10,186
Back off.

501
00:37:14,065 --> 00:37:14,982
Shall we have another?

502
00:37:18,069 --> 00:37:20,279
You know,
there's this new French restaurant…

503
00:37:35,169 --> 00:37:36,003
Ooh!

504
00:37:36,087 --> 00:37:38,422
- Oh, pardon! Hi.
- Hey! Great service tonight, ladies.

505
00:37:38,506 --> 00:37:40,174
- Thanks. You too.
- Have a good night.

506
00:37:40,258 --> 00:37:43,302
Thanks again for all your hard work
this year. We'll see you next year, huh?

507
00:37:43,386 --> 00:37:45,471
- Yes.
- Great. Have a good New Year's!

508
00:37:45,554 --> 00:37:48,724
- Have a good New Year, sir.
- Thanks. Thanks, everyone. See you soon.

509
00:37:48,808 --> 00:37:49,809
Bye-bye. Take care.

510
00:37:49,892 --> 00:37:52,019
- Should we grab a quick drink?
- Yeah! I know a place.

511
00:38:06,075 --> 00:38:09,161
Well, another eventful year behind us.
It was a good one though.

512
00:38:09,245 --> 00:38:10,788
Business is thriving.

513
00:38:11,455 --> 00:38:13,916
Yeah, well, when the Olympics happen,
that'll be something.

514
00:38:14,709 --> 00:38:16,377
Better for the economy too.

515
00:38:17,253 --> 00:38:19,130
Shinzan and Dahlia are both going strong.

516
00:38:19,213 --> 00:38:21,882
How about we open
a couple more clubs next year?

517
00:38:21,966 --> 00:38:23,217
Ah, we'll see.

518
00:38:24,677 --> 00:38:28,097
But I wouldn't mind getting a nice house.

519
00:38:28,597 --> 00:38:31,100
And then maybe starting a new business.

520
00:38:31,892 --> 00:38:33,227
New business?

521
00:38:33,311 --> 00:38:36,188
There's only so far
you can go with nightclubs.

522
00:38:36,772 --> 00:38:40,651
I want more. You know?
I wanna do something bigger.

523
00:38:41,444 --> 00:38:44,655
Ah, you better watch out.
The greed will get ya.

524
00:38:48,159 --> 00:38:48,993
Mm.

525
00:38:49,076 --> 00:38:50,786
Sudo-san.

526
00:38:51,287 --> 00:38:53,581
I'm sorry, sir,
but we're closed for the evening.

527
00:39:00,296 --> 00:39:01,255
Here it is.

528
00:39:01,797 --> 00:39:04,884
I'm in the middle
of… of a subdivision project in Karuizawa.

529
00:39:04,967 --> 00:39:05,801
Okay.

530
00:39:06,469 --> 00:39:10,181
But the thing is,
I've run into a bit of a problem.

531
00:39:10,264 --> 00:39:11,807
What kind of problem?

532
00:39:11,891 --> 00:39:17,438
We need to come up
with 500,000 yen by tomorrow morning,

533
00:39:18,356 --> 00:39:21,817
and, uh, normally,
that's just a drop in the ocean for me,

534
00:39:21,901 --> 00:39:24,111
but it's the end of the year,

535
00:39:24,779 --> 00:39:26,572
and all the banks are closed.

536
00:39:26,655 --> 00:39:29,325
So it's impossible for me
to get in touch with anyone.

537
00:39:32,495 --> 00:39:35,122
And so it's embarrassing for me, but…

538
00:39:36,916 --> 00:39:38,084
would you help?

539
00:39:38,167 --> 00:39:39,585
I'd be in your debt.

540
00:39:44,131 --> 00:39:45,591
I'd be happy to help.

541
00:39:47,635 --> 00:39:49,303
Excuse me a second.

542
00:39:49,387 --> 00:39:50,346
Of course.

543
00:39:51,013 --> 00:39:53,057
Ah, this whole thing seems fishy to me.

544
00:39:53,140 --> 00:39:54,016
I wouldn't do it.

545
00:39:54,100 --> 00:39:56,435
He's one of our biggest customers.
You know that.

546
00:39:56,519 --> 00:39:59,146
What if he kept throwing money around
because this was his goal?

547
00:39:59,230 --> 00:40:01,232
He's spent about 300,000 yen so far?

548
00:40:01,315 --> 00:40:03,234
So he still profits 200,000 this way.

549
00:40:03,317 --> 00:40:07,196
I doubt he'd go through that trouble
just to make 200,000 yen, Hisao.

550
00:40:12,493 --> 00:40:15,454
I can't thank you enough.
You really saved me.

551
00:40:15,538 --> 00:40:17,206
Oh, please. Not at all.

552
00:40:18,541 --> 00:40:22,753
But funnily enough, this is the first time
we've had a proper conversation.

553
00:40:22,837 --> 00:40:24,588
If I'm being frank,
you've been rather short.

554
00:40:24,672 --> 00:40:25,548
Ah.

555
00:40:26,757 --> 00:40:28,092
Well, honestly,

556
00:40:29,135 --> 00:40:31,470
I was just a little nervous around you.

557
00:40:32,555 --> 00:40:33,389
What?

558
00:40:34,932 --> 00:40:37,393
That day we ran into each other, remember?

559
00:40:39,145 --> 00:40:40,688
It was love at first sight.

560
00:40:44,442 --> 00:40:47,903
Sudo-san, I had no idea
you were such a charmer.

561
00:40:53,826 --> 00:40:54,743
Oh.

562
00:40:56,871 --> 00:40:59,039
No wonder it's so chilly out tonight.

563
00:41:07,923 --> 00:41:10,468
Well, I think I'll get going.

564
00:41:10,551 --> 00:41:11,552
Sure.

565
00:41:11,635 --> 00:41:13,095
Thank you so much again.

566
00:41:24,231 --> 00:41:25,774
Have a nice New Year!

567
00:41:28,235 --> 00:41:29,445
Yes! You too!

568
00:41:35,576 --> 00:41:37,786
I still think
he's trying to pull a fast one.

569
00:41:38,412 --> 00:41:40,289
If he is, then fine.

570
00:41:40,956 --> 00:41:42,333
I don't mind a bit.

571
00:41:47,630 --> 00:41:50,966
<i>And it was during</i>
<i>that very cold end-of-year night</i>

572
00:41:51,634 --> 00:41:53,844
<i>that delusion consumed me.</i>

573
00:41:55,930 --> 00:42:00,643
<i>Something new and exciting</i>
<i>was on the horizon that New Year.</i>

574
00:42:01,727 --> 00:42:03,812
<i>Or at least that's how it felt.</i>
